name: Gomer Pyle, U.S.M.C.
summary: Gomer Pyle, a naive country boy, leaves his home in Mayberry, NC to join the U.S. Marine corps. His perpetual wide-eyed innocence frequently gets on the nerves of his tough, loudmouthed sergeant.
description: Gomer Pyle, a naive country boy, leaves his home in Mayberry, NC to join the U.S. Marine corps. His perpetual wide-eyed innocence frequently gets on the nerves of his tough, loudmouthed sergeant.

episodes.name: Gomer Overcomes the Obstacle Course
episodes.description: Gomer gets his first shot at the obstacle course.

episodes.name: Guest in the Barracks
episodes.description: Gomer helps a recruit smuggle his girlfriend into the barracks.

episodes.name: Private Ralph Skunk
episodes.description: While on a hike Gomer makes a friend, but when the friend decides to move into the barracks Sgt Carter wants him gone! but Gomer shows the sergeant what an asset this new friend is to the platoon.

episodes.name: Captain Ironpants
episodes.description: After tipping his hat instead of saluting female Captain "Iron Pants" Martin, Gomer is assigned special detail in her office to teach him a lesson.

episodes.name: Gomer Learns a Bully
episodes.description: A trouble maker transfers into the platoon and decides to make Pyle his patsy, Gomer tries to handle it with understanding and kindness - but soon learns that bullies need to be stood up against.

episodes.name: Pay Day
episodes.description: After being bawled out by Sgt. Carter for not working hard enough Gomer decides not accept his pay for that week which causes all sorts of troubles for Sgt. Carter.

episodes.name: Nobody Loves a Sergeant
episodes.description: Sergeant Carter tries to make Gomer dislike him before graduation, feeling that he hasn't done his job correctly if he isn't hated by ALL the recruits.

episodes.name: Gomer and the Dragon Lady
episodes.description: While in town on pass Sgt. Carter decides to play a joke on Gomer by setting him on a quest to get a kiss from "The Dragon Lady" but in order for it to work he will need Duke's help.

episodes.name: Survival of the Fattest
episodes.description: It's Survival Training for the platoon: two-man teams must rough it for five days. Thinking Gomer will bring down the platoon's rating, Sgt. Carter takes him for his partner.

episodes.name: Sgt. Carter, Marine Babysitter
episodes.description: Gomer and his fellow Marines are headed into town on day passes when one of them is stuck on guard duty.

episodes.name: The Case of the Marine Bandit
episodes.description: While hitching a ride to town Gomer stops to help a stranded motorist, she takes him into town to meet her mother. A robber is holding up liquor stores while wearing a Marine's uniform at the same time.

episodes.name: Sergeant of the Week
episodes.description: A mix-up leads Carter to believe Gomer's dying.

episodes.name: Dance, Marine, Dance
episodes.description: Gomer's conned into signing a contract for dancing lessons.

episodes.name: Sergeant Carter Gets a 'Dear John' Letter
episodes.description: Carter asks Gomer to take his place on a date.

episodes.name: Daughter of the Sarge
episodes.description: Carter's adopted Korean daughter arrives, but she's not the little girl he remembers.

episodes.name: Officer Candidate Gomer Pyle
episodes.description: Carter tries for the Officer Candidate School.

episodes.name: Old Man Carter
episodes.description: Gomer tries to collect money for Carter's birthday.

episodes.name: Gomer Makes the Honor Guard
episodes.description: Carter may have to use Gomer as an honor guard since he owns a blue dress uniform.

episodes.name: My Buddy--War Hero
episodes.description: Carter and an old war buddy credit each other for being war heroes.

episodes.name: The Jet Set
episodes.description: Duke talks Gomer into taking a jeep to the airport.

episodes.name: Sergeant of the Guard
episodes.description: Gomer is a look-out for burglars robbing the base.

episodes.name: Gomer the M.P.
episodes.description: Gomer gets assigned to MP duty.

episodes.name: PFC Gomer Pyle
episodes.description: Carter wants his men to pass a promotion test.

episodes.name: Third Finger, Left Loaf
episodes.description: Gomer holds a wedding ring for a friend and it appears to be lost when they spend a night baking bread.

episodes.name: The Blind Date
episodes.description: Sergeant Carter's date has a friend she doesn't want to leave alone so she tells the Sergeant that it's a double date or nothing. As a last resort the Sergeant invites Pyle.

episodes.name: Home on the Range
episodes.description: Gomer meets a family from N. Carolina who have encountered truck problems en route to Oregon so Gomer puts them up in a blasting range cabin untill he has time to fix their truck.

episodes.name: Gomer Untrains a Dog
episodes.description: Gomer volunteers to train "Killer" a German Sheppard intended for sentry duty but turns Killer into a pussycat.

episodes.name: Supply Sergeants Never Die
episodes.description: When the supply Sgt is reluctant to go on vacation, Sgt Carter bets him any Knucklehead can take over his job. Of course, what bigger Knucklehead than Pyle to prove him right.

episodes.name: Cat Overboard
episodes.description: In the first of the 3 part sea maneuvers, Gomer sneaks a cat aboard a Navy ship, unaware there is sensitive Petty Chief Officer who throws all Contraband overboard.

episodes.name: Gomer Captures a Submarine
episodes.description: Part 2 of sea maneuvers has Pyle repeatedly goofing up Carter's mission.

episodes.name: The Grudge Fight
episodes.description: Part 3 of Sea Maneuvers, has Carter challenging the Petty Chief Officer to a boxing match not knowing the Chief was the Fleet Champ with 37 knockouts.

episodes.name: Gomer, State Witness
episodes.description: While sitting in a restaurant, Gomer witnesses an automobile accident between Sergeant Carter and another driver. When in court Gomer takes the oath seriously to tell the truth, the whole truth and nothing but the truth.

episodes.name: A Visit from Cousin Goober
episodes.description: When Gomer's cousin Goober shows up in the barracks and puts on one of Gomer's uniforms and then wanders the base, everyone sees the name Pyle on the uniform and thinks Gomer is losing his mind.

episodes.name: A Groom for Sergeant Carter's Sister
episodes.description: Gomer starts dating Sergeant Carter's sister. Carter is determined to break them up.

episodes.name: Gomer Minds His Sergeant's Car
episodes.description: Carter assigns Pyle to drive his precious car back from the airport but the car is stolen immediately. Now Pyle has 24 hours to find it before Carter gets back and kills him.

episodes.name: Gomer, the Peacemaker
episodes.description: Gomer won't rest until he helps to reunite Sergeant Carter with Miss Bunny after they had a lovers spat.

episodes.name: Gomer Pyle, POW
episodes.description: Gomer and his platoon engage in "war games" against a rival unit and Pvt. Pyle ends up captured and a prisoner of war.

episodes.name: Gomer Pyle, Civilian
episodes.description: Sergeant Carter orders Pyle to take a week long furlough but instead of going back home to Mayberry, Pyle takes a civilian job on base so he can remain close to the Sergeant.

episodes.name: Gomer and the Beast
episodes.description: Gomer's acts of kindness towards his new waitress friend is mistaken for romantic interest by her cruel Marine Sergeant boyfriend.

episodes.name: Grandma Pyle, Fortune Teller
episodes.description: Grandma Pyle visits Gomer, reads his fortune and predicts Gomer will cause something bad to happen; then Sergeant Carter loses his voice while yelling at him.

episodes.name: Little Girl Blue
episodes.description: A Colonel and his young daughter are visiting Camp Henderson. While befriending the little girl, Pyle has no problem getting her and himself in trouble with everyone.

episodes.name: A Star Is Born
episodes.description: Sgt. Carter is chosen to appear in a documentary but becomes an absurd camera hog, leaving producers no choice but to follow Gomer performing punishments Carter doles out.

episodes.name: Gomer and the Phone Company
episodes.description: After a pay phone spits out $41.75 in coins, Duke and Frankie are ecstatic about all the fun they can have spending it, but good Samaritan Gomer is determined to return it to the phone company.

episodes.name: Vacation in Vegas
episodes.description: Gomer wins a trip for two to Las Vegas and takes Sergeant Carter with him. The Sergeant has no money so he has to rely on Gomer for entertainment but Gomer has set an itinerary which include things like visiting a Rock Museum.

episodes.name: Opie Joins the Marines
episodes.description: Opie Taylor runs away from Mayberry to join the Marines.

episodes.name: A Date with Miss Camp Henderson
episodes.description: A bet between sergeants and Sergeant Carter's lies result in Gomer dating Miss Camp Henderson and taking her to Lookout Point.

episodes.name: Gomer and the Father Figure
episodes.description: Both Gomer and Sergeant Carter are conned by an old bum.

episodes.name: Desk Job for Sergeant Carter
episodes.description: Sergeant Carter takes a temporary desk job writing training manuals and considers making it permanent when he sees the platoon does fine without him; so Gomer messes things up to bring the Sergeant back.

episodes.name: Gomer, the Would-Be Hero
episodes.description: Sergeant Carter is in a restaurant with a girl other than his girlfriend when he foils an armed robbery. The Sergeant doesn't want his girlfriend to know he was there with another woman so he pins the credit on Gomer.
